## **Module 2: Network Infrastructure** (Domain 2.0 - 20% of exam)

### **Lesson 10: Ethernet Standards and Cabling**
**Time:** 25-30 minutes  
**Exam Objectives:** 2.1, 2.2 - Compare physical interface and cabling types

**Topics Covered:**
- Copper cabling
  - Twisted pair cable types
    - Cat 5e (1 Gbps, 100m)
    - Cat 6 (1 Gbps, 10 Gbps at 55m)
    - Cat 6a (10 Gbps, 100m)
    - Cat 7 (10 Gbps, shielded)
    - Cat 8 (40 Gbps, 30m)
  - UTP vs STP (shielded)
  - Coaxial cable (RG-6, RG-59)
  - Cable termination standards
    - T568A and T568B
    - Straight-through vs crossover
- Ethernet standards
  - 10BASE-T (10 Mbps)
  - 100BASE-TX (Fast Ethernet)
  - 1000BASE-T (Gigabit)
  - 10GBASE-T (10 Gigabit)
- Fiber optic cabling
  - Single-mode fiber (SMF) - long distance
  - Multi-mode fiber (MMF) - short distance
  - Fiber connectors (LC, SC, ST, MTRJ)
  - Wavelengths (850nm, 1310nm, 1550nm)
  - Ethernet over fiber
    - 1000BASE-SX, 1000BASE-LX
    - 10GBASE-SR, 10GBASE-LR
- Transceivers and media converters
- SFP, SFP+, QSFP modules
- Cable distance limitations
- Plenum vs non-plenum rated cable

---

### **Lesson 11: Switches, VLANs, and Trunking**
**Time:** 30-35 minutes  
**Exam Objectives:** 2.1, 2.3 - Network devices and VLANs

**Topics Covered:**
- Switch fundamentals
  - How switches work (MAC address tables)
  - Layer 2 switching
  - Collision domains vs broadcast domains
  - Switch forwarding methods
- MAC address tables
  - Learning
  - Flooding
  - Forwarding
  - Filtering
  - Aging
- VLANs (Virtual LANs)
  - Purpose of VLANs
  - VLAN benefits (security, performance, organization)
  - VLAN IDs (1-4094)
  - Default VLAN (VLAN 1)
  - Data VLANs
  - Voice VLANs
  - Native VLAN
  - Management VLAN
- Trunking
  - 802.1Q tagging
  - VLAN tagging
  - Trunk ports vs access ports
  - Allowed VLANs on trunks
- Inter-VLAN routing
  - Router on a stick (ROAS)
  - Layer 3 switch (SVI)
- Spanning Tree Protocol (STP)
  - Purpose: prevent loops
  - Root bridge election
  - Port states (blocking, listening, learning, forwarding)
  - RSTP (Rapid Spanning Tree)
- Port security
- Port mirroring (SPAN)

---

### **Lesson 12: Routing Fundamentals and Protocols**
**Time:** 30-35 minutes  
**Exam Objectives:** 2.1, 2.2 - Routing concepts and protocols

**Topics Covered:**
- Routing fundamentals
  - What is routing
  - Routing table
  - Default gateway
  - Static routes vs dynamic routes
  - Administrative distance
  - Routing metrics (hop count, bandwidth, delay)
- Routing protocols
  - Distance vector vs link state vs hybrid
  - Interior vs Exterior Gateway Protocols
- RIP (Routing Information Protocol)
  - Distance vector
  - Hop count metric (max 15)
  - RIPv1 vs RIPv2
  - Slow convergence
- OSPF (Open Shortest Path First)
  - Link state protocol
  - Cost metric (based on bandwidth)
  - Areas and Area 0 (backbone)
  - DR and BDR (Designated Router)
  - Fast convergence
  - Scalable
- EIGRP (Enhanced Interior Gateway Routing Protocol)
  - Hybrid protocol (Cisco proprietary)
  - Composite metric
  - Fast convergence
- BGP (Border Gateway Protocol)
  - Exterior gateway protocol
  - Path vector protocol
  - Used on the internet between ISPs
  - AS (Autonomous System) numbers
- Route summarization/aggregation
- Routing loops and prevention

---

### **Lesson 13: Wireless Networking (Wi-Fi 6/6E, 802.11)**
**Time:** 30-35 minutes  
**Exam Objectives:** 2.4 - Wireless standards and technologies

**Topics Covered:**
- Wireless standards (802.11)
  - 802.11a (5 GHz, 54 Mbps)
  - 802.11b (2.4 GHz, 11 Mbps)
  - 802.11g (2.4 GHz, 54 Mbps)
  - 802.11n (Wi-Fi 4) - dual band, 600 Mbps
  - 802.11ac (Wi-Fi 5) - 5 GHz, multi-gigabit
  - 802.11ax (Wi-Fi 6/6E) - 2.4/5/6 GHz, improved efficiency
- Wireless frequencies
  - 2.4 GHz band (channels 1, 6, 11 non-overlapping)
  - 5 GHz band (more channels, less interference)
  - 6 GHz band (Wi-Fi 6E only)
- Wireless channels and channel bonding
- MIMO (Multiple Input Multiple Output)
- MU-MIMO (Multi-User MIMO)
- Beamforming
- SSID (Service Set Identifier)
  - Broadcasting vs hidden
- Wireless modes
  - Infrastructure (AP-based)
  - Ad-hoc (peer-to-peer)
- Wireless encryption (covered in security module)
- Wireless site surveys
- Heat maps
- Roaming and handoff
- Wireless controllers
- Wireless mesh networks

---

### **Lesson 14: Network Devices (Routers, Firewalls, Load Balancers)**
**Time:** 25-30 minutes  
**Exam Objectives:** 2.1 - Compare and contrast various devices

**Topics Covered:**
- Networking devices overview
- **Layer 1 devices:**
  - Hubs (obsolete)
  - Repeaters
  - Media converters
- **Layer 2 devices:**
  - Switches
  - Bridges
  - Wireless Access Points (WAPs)
- **Layer 3 devices:**
  - Routers
  - Layer 3 switches (multilayer)
- **Security devices:**
  - Firewalls (stateful, stateless, next-gen)
  - IDS (Intrusion Detection System)
  - IPS (Intrusion Prevention System)
  - Unified Threat Management (UTM)
- **Optimization devices:**
  - Load balancers (Layer 4 and Layer 7)
  - Proxy servers (forward, reverse)
  - Content filters
  - VPN concentrators
- **Other devices:**
  - Modems
  - VoIP devices (phones, gateways)
  - Controllers (wireless, SDN)
  - Network attached storage (NAS)
  - Storage area network (SAN)
- Device placement in network design

